Combine buttermilk and pepper sauce in pie plate. Mix flour and salt on waxed paper. Dip chicken into buttermilk, then coat with flour; repeat once. Heat 1/4 inch oil in large nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken, in batches, 5 minutes, or until deep golden and juices run clear when thickest part of chicken is pierced. Transfer to paper towels to drain. Toss salad mix and tomatoes with dressing in large shallow bowl until evenly coated. Top with chicken.